      "span_text": "In general, two-dimensional flows dominated by vortex structures are neither stationary nor uniformly moving, but it has been observed that these flows evolve slowly between a succession of quasi-steady states, except during rapid vortex mergers.  Two equal vortices located in an otherwise quiescent fluid rotate initially around the midpoint of the line joining their centers.",
